The paper deals with video grounding, which involves understanding the relationship between language and visual information. This falls under the intersection of computer vision (cs.CV) and natural language processing (cs.CL). The paper also proposes a novel Spatio-Temporal Graph Reasoning Network (STGRN) for this task, which involves graph reasoning and selection methods, indicating a potential fit for machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper introduces a new dataset, VidSTG, which involves video analysis and annotation, indicating a potential fit for multimedia (cs.MM).
